In this lecture course, the main trends in the methodology of legal research, their historical context and current problems are discussed in depth. In the seminars, doctoral students' research projects are discussed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Gaining experience in presentation, opposition, moderation and discussion; developing the methodological knowledge and skills needed to design and compile a scientific article or chapter of a monograph with legal content.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the doctoral student: knows the different directions of the methodology of legal research, as well as their historical context; is aware of the possibilities of different methodological approaches; is able to critically evaluate and apply methods suitable for legal research; is able to critically evaluate the application of legal methods.
